Benue State Governor Samuel Ortom on Monday confirmed that seven persons were killed and five seriously injured as suspected herdsmen attacked Anune community in Makurdi Local Government area of the state. The assailants invaded the community on Saturday night. Speaking to reporters shortly after visiting St.Theresa’s Hospital in Makurdi, where those injured in the attack have been receiving treatment, Governor Ortom reiterated his administration’s resolve to implement the anti-open grazing law in the state no matter the intimidation. He told reporters that the law must be implemented because it is a creation of the state lawmakers. Ortom directed that those killed in the attack be given mass burial today, adding that his administration will foot the medical bills of the injured in the attack. Anune is a suburb of Makurdi, the state capital.